10/08/2008
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Two people died and five were injured in a storm in the central part of the country on Saturday (August 9th). A woman and her daughter were killed by a lightning strike near the town of Zenica. Her husband and their son were injured in the incident. Another woman and two girls were injured after a tree fell in the town of Jajce. Material damage included crushed cars and damaged roofs. (AFP, RTRS, SRNA, Dnevni Avaz, Fena - 09/08/08)
